cred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Roger de Avenel was born in 1190, in Eskdale District, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Gervase d'Avenel, was 51 and his mother, Sybilla Gervase of Eskdale, was 29. He married Maria de Graham in 1216, in Dumfriesshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1243, in his hometown, at the age of 53."},"et":{"1190–1243":"1190–1243","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1194–Male":"1194–Surnud","1196–Male":"1196–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1190–1257":"1190–1257","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","1229–Female":"1229–Surnud","1140–1219":"1140–1219","1162–Female":"1162–Surnud","1190":"1190","1216":"1216","1257":"1257","1210":"1210","1243":"1243","1196":"1196","1162":"1162","1140":"1140","1194":"1194","1219":"1219","1229":"1229","Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Eskdale Castle, Langhom, Dumfrieshire, Scotland":"Eskdale District, Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Eskdale Castle, Langhom, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Eskdale District, Dumfriesshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Eskdale, Dumfries, Scotland":"Eskdale District, Dumfriesshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1190–1243":"1190–1243","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1194–Male":"1194–Kuollut","1196–Male":"1196–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1190–1257":"1190–1257","1210–Female":"1210–Kuollut","1229–Female":"1229–Kuollut","1140–1219":"1140–1219","1162–Female":"1162–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1216":"1216","1257":"1257","1210":"1210","1243":"1243","1196":"1196","1162":"1162","1140":"1140","1194":"1194","1219":"1219","1229":"1229","Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Eskdale Castle, Langhom, Dumfrieshire, Scotland":"Eskdale District, Dumfriesshire